The paper deals with access control and security, which are typically covered in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of formal languages and automated tools suggests a focus on logic and verification, which are covered in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories. The use of Maude and Isabelle also suggests a focus on programming languages and semantics, which are covered in cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Finally, the use of automated tools for searching and proving suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, which is covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
